									<h4>Alternatives to Sachet Packaging</h4><p>While sachets remain a staple for convenient and cost-effective packaging, there are several alternative options worth considering, each with its own set of benefits and trade-offs:</p><ul><li><strong>Small bottles and jars:</strong> These rigid containers provide better protection and allow products to stand upright on shelves, enhancing presentation. However, their additional weight and bulk often lead to higher transport costs and greater use of storage space.</li><li><strong>Tubes:</strong> Ideal for pastes, gels, and creams, tubes are flexible and provide good control during dispensing. Although more robust than sachets, they are typically less space-efficient when empty or in bulk transport.</li><li><strong>Stand-up pouches:</strong> These flexible packages can be displayed upright and offer visual appeal similar to bottles, while remaining lighter and requiring less space during shipping. They generally balance transport efficiency with improved shelf presence, but may come at a slightly higher cost than flat sachets.</li></ul><p>When selecting a packaging method, consider factors like product type, required shelf presence, transportation cost, and shelf life so you can choose the solution that best matches your needs.</p>								</div>
