									<p>The NP-LS Automatic shrink sleeve label machine is used in the packaging and labeling process of various products, and is suitable for round bottles, flat bottles, square bottles, curved bottles, cups and other products in light industrial industries such as food and beverage, medical, and daily chemicals. The machine is also adaptable for pharmaceutical, health-food, beverage, juice, milk, and similar products—making it a versatile solution for a wide range of applications across multiple sectors.</p><h3>Flexible for Bottles and Caps Alike</h3><p>Whether you’re labeling bottles, caps, or a mix of both, the NP-LS Automatic Shrink Sleeve Label Machine has you covered. Thanks to its adaptable design, it accommodates a variety of container shapes—round, square, flat, or curved—and works equally well for caps in addition to full bottles. With multiple models available to suit different production speeds, from small runs to high-volume lines (150 to 550 pieces per minute), there’s a configuration to match just about any need.</p><h3>Need to switch formats?</h3><p>The machine can be easily adjusted for different package widths, heights, and shapes, ensuring compatibility across your product range without hassle.</p><h3>Available Models of Shrink Sleeve Labeling Machines</h3><p>When it comes to shrink sleeve labeling, there are a variety of models designed to fit different production needs and packaging shapes. Depending on your requirements, options typically include:</p><ul><li>Standalone Automatic Sleeve Labelers: Designed for seamless integration into production lines, these units handle everything from sleeve application to shrinking in a fully automated process.</li><li>Inline Sleeve Applicators: Ideal for high-speed environments, these systems efficiently apply shrink sleeves to bottles and containers as they move through the conveyor line.</li><li>Standard Shrink Sleeve Applicators: Perfect for standard-sized bottles or containers, these models offer reliability and consistent performance for most bottling needs.</li></ul><p>Whether you need a compact solution for limited space or a high-capacity machine for demanding production lines, there’s a shrink sleeve model to fit.</p>								</div>
