				<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-e8596bc elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor" data-id="e8596bc" data-element_type="widget" data-e-type="widget" data-widget_type="text-editor.default">
									<h3>Types of Hot Melt Glue Labeling Machines</h3><p>Hot melt glue labeling technology offers a range of solutions to match various production needs and container types. Depending on your packaging requirements, you can choose from several machine styles purpose-built for specific labeling challenges:</p><ul><li>Roll-fed Labelers: These machines apply rolled plastic or paper labels—such as OPP or BOPP—directly onto cylindrical bottles at high speeds, making them ideal for beverages and other high-volume applications.</li><li>Flat Surface and Canister Labelers: For canisters, rectangular bottles, or containers with flat faces, dedicated models ensure the precise placement of glued paper or film labels, eliminating the frustrations that can come with tricky container geometries.</li><li>Stack-fed Labelers: Designed to handle pre-cut paper labels, these systems separate and feed each label, apply adhesive, and then affix the label to the container. They&#8217;re a smart fit for operations requiring flexibility in label shapes and materials.</li><li>High-Speed Solutions: Where volume is king, fully automated labeling machines featuring rotary platforms and servo-driven mechanisms deliver rapid, reliable application for both paper and plastic labels—keeping pace with even the fastest production lines.</li></ul><p>With options tailored for cylindrical, rectangular, and specialty containers, hot melt glue labeling machines bring efficiency and adaptability to brands across food, beverages, pharmaceuticals, and more.</p>								</div>
