				<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-a626ebd elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor" data-id="a626ebd" data-element_type="widget" data-e-type="widget" data-widget_type="text-editor.default">
									<p>It integrates multiple functions into a seamless process, including automatic cap sorting and feeding, cap loading, vacuumizing, and capping, making it a multifunctional solutions for industries like food, beverages, pickle production, and cosmetics. </p><h3>How is an internal vacuum created during the capping process?</h3><p>Operationally, the Automatic Twist-off Cap Vacuum Lug Capping machine works by reducing the air pressure inside the bottle using a rapid steam injection method, ensuring the cap is tightly secured. It then creates a vacuum by applying cold water over the bottle. An elastomeric lining within the cap seals any gaps between the cap and bottle neck as the internal vacuum pulls them tightly together. This internal vacuum is achieved by filling the container with a hot product or by injecting steam just prior to capping; as the steam condenses inside, it creates a nearly perfect vacuum, locking in freshness and preserving product quality.</p>								</div>
